					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Relabeling things a little:<div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;.--\/--.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;/ROMSEL |01&nbsp; 16| +5V<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; SNES A15 |02&nbsp; 15| Pin 04<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; SNES A15 |03&nbsp; 14| SNES A20<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Pin 15 |04&nbsp; 13| SNES A21<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; NC |05&nbsp; 12| NC<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; NC |06&nbsp; 11| NC<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;ROM /CE |07&nbsp; 10| NC<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;GND |08&nbsp; 09| RAM /CE<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;'------'<br /></div>This is consistent with <a href="http://problemkaputt.de/fullsnes.htm#snespinoutsmadchips" class="postlink">nocash's description of the MAD-1</a>-<br /><br />(namely, when jumpered for LoROM, /ROMCE is low when /ROMSEL is low and SNES A15 is high, and /RAMCE is low when /ROMSEL and SNES A15 are low AND SNES A20, A21, and A22 are high)<br /><br />SNES A22 doesn't explicitly need to be decoded because A22 is necessarily high if /ROMSEL and SNES A15 are low.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

